The pandemic of the coronovirus 2019–20 is an ongoing disease pandemic by coronovirus 2019 (COVID-19), caused by coronovirus 2 of the severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS-CoV-2).
The outbreak was identified in Wuhan, China, in December 2019, as an international emergency of public health on 30 January 2020, and was recognized as a pandemic on 11 March 2020.
